"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-simone-biles-bears-games-attending-2024\", \"text\": \"American gymnast Simone Biles is a busy woman.  A little over two weeks after she won gold in the women's individual all-around final at the Summer Olympics in Paris, Biles was back on American soil cheering on her husband\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Chicago Bearssafety Jonathan Owens. Owens recorded three tackles in the Bears' 27\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00933 exhibition win over theCincinnati BengalsSaturday.  In a MondayTikTok, however, Biles revealed that she will likely attend few Bears games this season\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094because of her post-Olympic obligations.  \\\"I do not know how many games I will be able to make because in a few weeks we go on tour, and if you guys are not aware, it's the Gold Over America tour. I think right now we are doing about 32 stops,\\\" Biles said.  The tour, a traveling gymnastics exhibition featuring Biles and a spate of other gymnasts, is scheduled to commence Sept. 16 in Oceanside, Calif.  Chicago opens its season eight days prior against theTennessee Titans.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Patrick Andres is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated. He joined SI in December 2022, having worked for The Blade, Athlon Sports, Fear the Sword and Diamond Digest. Andres has covered everything from zero-attendance Big Ten basketball to a seven-overtime college football game. He is a graduate of Northwestern University's Medill School of Journalism with a double major in history .  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and